HEADWORD: Salivary
<hw>Sal"i*va*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>salivarius</ets> slimy, clammy: cf. F. <ets>salivaire</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to saliva; producing or
carrying saliva; <as>as, the <ex>salivary</ex> ferment; the
<ex>salivary</ex> glands; the <ex>salivary</ex> ducts,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Salivate</ent>⟦br⟧
